parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unintended acceleration of the vehicle during braking can lead to accidents, injuries, or fatalities, especially if the vehicle is traveling at high speeds or in heavy traffic.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates unexpectedly while braking
the brakes fail to respond to added pressure
the vehicle surges forward
the engine RPM increases suddenly
the vehicle lunges forward
the brakes make a scrubbing sound.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brakes can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The brakes fail to respond to added pressure
the vehicle fails to stop
the brakes make a scrubbing sound
the vehicle accelerates unexpectedly while braking.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the electronic transmission can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The transmission jumps into park from drive
the vehicle is unable to move
the transmission repeatedly jumps into park from drive.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden shattering of the sunroof can cause distractions, loss of control, and potentially lead to accidents, especially at high speeds.
symptoms: The sunroof shatters without any apparent impact or warning
often accompanied by a loud noise
and may occur in cold temperatures.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The transmission malfunction can cause unexpected delays or loss of control, leading to potential accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: The transmission switches to park from drive while at a stop
often intermittently
and may only occur in standard or economy mode.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The uncontrolled engine revving can cause loss of control, accidents, or near-misses, especially when stopping or slowing down.
symptoms: The engine starts revving uncontrollably
often maintaining excessive speed
and may stop after a short period.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure to perform a recall can lead to potential safety risks, as the recalled component may not be repaired or replaced.
symptoms: The dealership refuses to perform a scheduled recall
often citing lack of time or resources.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden opening of the rear hatch can cause distractions, loss of control, and potentially lead to accidents, especially when loading or unloading cargo.
symptoms: The rear hatch comes down without warning while loading or unloading items
often with no apparent cause or warning.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Catastrophic engine failure can cause the vehicle to lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: Loss of power
inability to accelerate
warning lights on the dashboard (e.g.
"N" for neutral
transmission malfunction)
no power
unable to start.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Timing chain guide failure can cause catastrophic engine failure, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: Low oil pressure warning light
drive train warning light
engine failure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Delayed recall repair can lead to catastrophic engine failure, accidents, or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: None reported
as the issue is related to the delay in recall repair.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended acceleration can cause accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: RPMs increase when the brake pedal is depressed
vehicle crashes into objects.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Diesel emissions system failure can cause environmental harm, decreased fuel efficiency, and increased maintenance costs.
symptoms: Early failure of diesel emissions system
replacement of NOx sensors
upper O2 sensor
and DPF filter.
